Description: Fragment of round handle at neck join from a Brindisi pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pale buff. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Antiochos. cf. Desy, Ph., Les timbres amphoriques de l'Apulie republicaine (Oxford 1989) 171. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 201, 20 or 55, 8.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1282)
